```
However, when I amend the line to this, do I get the correct conversion. 
`barg = 100000000 * bar; offset: 101325000 = bar_gauge`

```python
Q_(0, 'barg').to('bar')
>>> 1.01325 bar
```

In fact, it doesn't appear that the bar unit above has any effect as I can have the line read:
`barg = 100000000 * pascal; offset: 101325000 = bar_gauge`
and still convert properly.

Thanks",{},{}
