1195,IssuesEvent,2018-06-19 03:50:44+00:00,16331291,davisking/dlib,61218,xsacha,,,opened,GCC compile makes DNN generate random numbers,[],[],0,"## Expected Behavior
DNN generated result should be the same as in Clang and MSVC. It should also be a consistent number.

## Current Behavior
On GCC, after generating a DNN, a random number is returned. It seems to happen on every model I have attempted.

## Steps to Reproduce

CMake arguments:
# Use CPU generation (not CUDA!!!)
DLIB_USE_CUDA=OFF
USE_SSE4_INSTRUCTIONS=ON
DLIB_HEADER_ONLY=OFF
DLIB_ISO_CPP_ONLY=OFF
DLIB_NO_GUI_SUPPORT=ON
DLIB_ENABLE_ASSERTS=OFF
DLIB_ENABLE_STACK_TRACE=OFF
DLIB_JPEG_SUPPORT=OFF
DLIB_PNG_SUPPORT=OFF
DLIB_GIF_SUPPORT=OFF
DLIB_LINK_WITH_SQLITE3=OFF

Code:
```
my_model_96::anet_type model;
dlib::deserialize(resnet_model.string()) >> model;
std::vector<genitem> results;
std::vector<dlib::matrix<unsigned char>> probes;
results.reserve(128);
probes.reserve(128);
size_t count = q.wait_dequeue_bulk(std::back_inserter(results), 128);
for (size_t i = 0; i < count; ++i)
{
    dlib::matrix<unsigned char, 96, 96> img_resize;
    dlib::assign_image(img_resize, dlib::cv_image<unsigned char>(results[i].image));
    probes.emplace_back(std::move(img_resize));
}
std::vector<dlib::matrix<float, 0, 1>> probe_descriptors = model(probes);
for (int i = 0; i < results.size(); ++i)
{
    results[i].task.set_value(std::move(probe_descriptors[i]));
}

```

Sorry if this code is simplistic or missing something. Any model I use seems to fail.




* **Version**: 19.12 (does not happen on earlier versions AFAIK)
* **Where did you get dlib**: Hunter
* **Platform**: Linux x86-64
* **Compiler**: GCC 6.3 and GCC 8.1 tested (failing). Clang 4-6 and MSVC 2017 working as expected.
",{},{}
