1331,IssuesEvent,2017-02-10 22:36:12+00:00,15367540,jruizgit/rules,6834667,jgluna,,,opened,Issue with regular expressions,[],[],0,"Hello.

I have an issue with the matches statement in the Ruby implementation. Here is the code:

```
Durable.ruleset :split_itinerary do
  when_all (m.subject.matches(""/.*?(\d{2}-?\w{3}-?\d{2}\/)?-?(\w{3,6}\*?)(-\d{8})?-(\w{4})(-\d{4})?-(\w{1}).*/"")) do
    splitted = m.subject.split(""//"").select{|segment| segment.match(/.*?(\d{2}-?\w{3}-?\d{2}\/)?-?(\w{3,6}\*?)(-\d{8})?-(\w{4})(-\d{4})?-(\w{1})/)}
    i=1
    splitted.each do |segment|
      post :domestic_trip,{:id=>m.id, :sid=>m.sid.to_s+i.to_s, :segment=>segment}
      i=i+1
    end
  end
  when_start do
    post :split_itinerary, {:id=>1, :sid=>2, :subject =>""PYA/QF/RQ:18FEB17//SYDADL*-QFQF-X//PER-QFQF-X//BME-QFQF-X//DRW-QFQF-X//BNE*-QFQF-X//SYD-QFQF-U//N""}
  end
end

Durable.ruleset :domestic_trip do
  when_all (m.segment !="""") do
    puts ""segment => #{m.segment}""
  end
end

Durable.run_all
```

The regular expression at the when_all statement in the :split_itinerary rule is working regularly in ruby but not in here, actually, the application stalls when the rules are being loaded.

Is there a way to use regular expressions? Or, if it's something else, it would be nice to have it in the documentation.

I'm using 
Ruby version 2.4.0
Durable rules version 0.34.19",{},{}
