1729,IssuesEvent,2016-08-26 19:39:31+00:00,27283062,ktbyers/netmiko,899716,ktbyers,,,opened,Alcatel SROS Issues,[],[],0,"1.       commands are auto extended

a.       for example “show port desc | match 1/2/1”

b.  extends to “show port description | match 1/2/1”

c.       issue with “strip_command(command_string, output)”

 

2.       prompt can add/remove leading *

a.       indicates unsaved changes

b.      if present “admin save” will remove it

c.       if not present config change will add it

d.      ex:

A:2xxxxxxB_T# configure port 1/1/1 no shutdown
*A:2xxxxxxB_T# admin save
Writing configuration to cf3:\config.cfg
Saving configuration ... OK
Completed.
A:2xxxxxxB_T#
 
3.       exec -echo <filename>

a.       in my environment I regularly generate a script file, (review), ftp it to router, then execute

b.      –echo is good for logging purposes but not really necessary

c.       After exec (with echo option) each command in file is execute as if the user entered it

d.      Prompt confusion, highlighted text was output after exec command (not input)

e.      ex.

A:2xxxxxxB_T# exec -echo test.txt
A:2xxxxxxB_T# exit all
A:2xxxxxxB_T# configure port 1/1/1
A:2xxxxxxB_T>config>port# no shut
A:2xxxxxxB_T>config>port# exit all
A:2xxxxxxB_T# admin save
Writing configuration to cf3:\config.cfg
Saving configuration ... OK
Completed.
Executed 5 lines in 0.3 seconds from file cf3:\test.txt
A:2xxxxxxB_T#",{},{}
