2698,IssuesEvent,2017-11-14 20:15:53+00:00,9405260,kz26/PyExcelerate,511342,kevmo314,,,closed,Timezone-unaware inner date,"[{'id': 35702688, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/kz26/PyExcelerate/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}]",[],2,"PyExcelerate doesn't work for timezone-aware datetimes.
Error is raised when you pass some timezone-aware datetime to be written.

This forces users to coerce their datetimes to strings first or delete related timezone info before write.

Error place is there
```python
@staticmethod
	def to_excel_date(d):
		if isinstance(d, datetime):
			delta = d - DataTypes.EXCEL_BASE_DATE
			excel_date = delta.days + (float(delta.seconds) + float(delta.microseconds) / 1E6) / (60 * 60 * 24) + 1
			return excel_date + (excel_date > 59)
		elif isinstance(d, date):
			# this is why python sucks >.<
			return DataTypes.to_excel_date(datetime(*(d.timetuple()[:6])))
		elif isinstance(d, time):
			return DataTypes.to_excel_date(datetime(*(DataTypes.EXCEL_BASE_DATE.timetuple()[:3]), hour=d.hour, minute=d.minute, second=d.second, microsecond=d.microsecond)) - 1
```

http://joxi.ru/GrqGQdTQ7NXE2z.png",{},{}
