2960,IssuesEvent,2016-12-22 17:49:52+00:00,1938370,Mottie/tablesorter,24481435,rnesolydev,,,closed,Group widget and IE7 issue,"[{'id': 153147, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Mottie/tablesorter/labels/How%20To...', 'name': 'How To...', 'color': 'fbca04', 'default': False}, {'id': 153150, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Mottie/tablesorter/labels/Will%20not%20fix', 'name': 'Will not fix', 'color': 'e102d8', 'default': False}]",[],4,"I am having a problem using the group option with IE7 (I know, I should not have to support IE7 but I do, they force IE to version 7 here where I work).

It seems to be working on IE8 and above but not below.

I am getting ""Member not found"" in my jquery.js file (v 1.7)  I have tried newer version up thru 1.9 all the same issue.    

I am using tablesorter version v2.28.1.

The error is occurring on the return ""**return ( ret.nodeValue = value + """" );**"".  See code below.  

Does anyone know a workaround for this issue?
```

// IE6/7 do not support getting/setting some attributes with get/setAttribute
if ( !getSetAttribute ) {

	fixSpecified = {
		name: true,
		id: true
	};

	// Use this for any attribute in IE6/7
	// This fixes almost every IE6/7 issue
	nodeHook = jQuery.valHooks.button = {
		get: function( elem, name ) {
			var ret;
			ret = elem.getAttributeNode( name );
			return ret && ( fixSpecified[ name ] ? ret.nodeValue !== """" : ret.specified ) ?
				ret.nodeValue :
				undefined;
		},
		set: function( elem, value, name ) {
			// Set the existing or create a new attribute node
			var ret = elem.getAttributeNode( name );
			if ( !ret ) {
				ret = document.createAttribute( name );
				elem.setAttributeNode( ret );
			}
			return ( ret.nodeValue = value + """" );
		}
	};

```
Here is my script for sorting and grouping my gridview ...

```
 <script type=""text/javascript"">
