To repro:
- mtools 1.2.1 and pymongo 2.7.2 installed
- `pip install mtools --upgrade`
- run `mlaunch --replicaset --arbiter --port 30000 --nodes 2`

Commands like `mlaunch list` and `mlaunch stop` will fail with a traceback similar to:

```
mlaunch list
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""/usr/local/bin/mlaunch"", line 9, in <module>
    load_entry_point('mtools==1.2.2', 'console_scripts', 'mlaunch')()
  File ""/Library/Python/2.7/site-packages/mtools/mlaunch/mlaunch.py"", line 1410, in main
    tool.run()
  File ""/Library/Python/2.7/site-packages/mtools/mlaunch/mlaunch.py"", line 259, in run
    getattr(self, self.args['command'])()
  File ""/Library/Python/2.7/site-packages/mtools/mlaunch/mlaunch.py"", line 555, in list
    self.discover()
  File ""/Library/Python/2.7/site-packages/mtools/mlaunch/mlaunch.py"", line 803, in discover
    self.cluster_tags['primary'].append( mrsc.primary[1] )
  File ""/Library/Python/2.7/site-packages/pymongo/database.py"", line 211, in __getitem__
    return self.__getattr__(name)
  File ""/Library/Python/2.7/site-packages/pymongo/database.py"", line 201, in __getattr__
    return Collection(self, name)
  File ""/Library/Python/2.7/site-packages/pymongo/collection.py"", line 101, in __init__
    ""of %s"" % (basestring.__name__,))
```

Manually installing latest PyMongo should fix:
  `pip install pymongo --upgrade`

Check version of PyMongo:
  `python -c ""import pymongo; print(pymongo.version);""`
",{},{}
3259,IssuesEvent,2018-08-12 16:28:47+00:00,116512808,scottbonline/sense,3783553,kbickar,,,closed,Slamming Sense's internal API with authentication requests,[],"[{'login': 'kbickar', 'id': 3783553, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjM3ODM1NTM=', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/3783553?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kbickar', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/kbickar', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kbickar/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kbickar/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kbickar/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kbickar/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kbickar/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kbickar/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kbickar/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kbickar/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kbickar/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",3,"[https://community.sense.com/t/download-or-api-to-feed-pvoutput/3033/25](https://community.sense.com/t/download-or-api-to-feed-pvoutput/3033/25)

RyanAtSense
Community Manager

Hey guys. It’s come to the engineering team’s attention that the unofficial APIs posted are slamming our internal API with authentication requests pretty much constantly. This is causing some performance degradation on our end. We have no issue with these APIs existing and being utilized by our userbase, but they should not be coded in such a way as to negatively affect performance for our teams and the rest of our users. We’ve contacted the owners of both Github repositories so they can make the necessary changes to their code.",{},{}
