4247,IssuesEvent,2017-02-09 09:51:43+00:00,6054289,niklasf/python-chess,7028169,salvador-dali,,,opened,"Variants, Racing King. Incorrect draw detection",[],[],0,"There are a few cases where Racing King variant report incorrect variant-ending due to the stalemate

 - `4Q1K1/8/7k/4R3/8/5B2/8/3N4 b - - 0 0`
 - `1Q4R1/5K2/4B3/8/8/3N4/8/k7 b - - 0 0`
 - `8/kr6/q2n4/8/7K/3r4/3bb3/8 w - - 0 0`
 - `7R/3R4/5K2/B1k5/5N2/8/2N3Q1/5B2 b - - 0 0`
As you see, here white/black has to move, but can't because it is in a stalemating position. Notice that in the first example white already reached the last position, but it is still a draw because black has the last chance to move.",{},{}
