4303,IssuesEvent,2016-10-24 10:25:04+00:00,70476160,stedmeister/easyargs,426859,dannystaple,,,opened,Support sphinx docstring param descriptions,[],[],0,"In sphinx, and a number of IDE's the parameters for a function can be documented in the docstring for a function:

    """"""
    :param foo: Stuff to do blah
    :param bar: Other stuff
    """"""

I propose supporting this so when specified it becomes the help.
Taking one of your examples (which will seem contrived, but more complex examples make it more necessary):

```
@easyargs
def main(name, count=1, greeting='Hello'):
    """"""A simple greeting program
    :param name:      Name to greet.
    :param count:     How many times to greet them.
    :param greeting:  Which greeting to use..
    """"""
    for i in range(count):
        print '{greeting} {name}!'.format(greeting=greeting, name=name)
```

The help output would then look like this:
```
$ python simple.py -h
usage: simple_test.py [-h] [--count COUNT] [--greeting GREETING] name

A simple greeting program

positional arguments:
  name                 Name to greet.

optional arguments:
  -h, --help           show this help message and exit
  --count COUNT        How many times to greet them.
  --greeting GREETING  Which greeting to use.
```

",{},{}
