5201,IssuesEvent,2018-08-21 02:56:38+00:00,143541475,kylebarron/stata_kernel,15164633,kylebarron,,,closed,Set more to x number of pages?,[],[],6,"Currently on starting, the kernel does `set more off`. If someone loads a 1 million row dataset and types `list`, 1 million rows of the data will be printed on the screen or until the user `KeyboardInterrupt`s. This is probably undesirable, as some users won't know to `Ctrl-C`, and it's slightly different on Hydrogen and Jupyter Notebook.

So probably set `set more 10` or something at the beginning, and then also `expect` for `\r\n--more--`. Then if you hit that, automatically press `q` and tell user that output was shortened by `more`.

Note that `set more 1` doesn't work for shell commands. `!yes` runs forever.",{},{}
5210,IssuesEvent,2017-01-12 12:38:26+00:00,9376661,lorenzofox3/Smart-Table,25079330,cbayleyball,,,opened,Unable to initialize multiple search fields,[],[],0,"I've done the search and didn't find anything that seemed to match my problem.  I am using Smart Table 2.0.1 and Angular 1.3.16.  Unfortunately I cannot provide a plunkr since my application is being developed on a closed system, but I will try to describe it as much as possible.

My smart table has multiple column search fields defined as follows:

<input id=""field1"" ng-model=""field1"" st-search=""field1"" type=""search>
<input id=""field2"" ng-model=""field2"" st-search=""field2"" type=""search>

The search fields work beautifully but I want to add a default value to both of them (based on parameters passed to the page) and initially filter the table.  So I added the following to the angular controller:

$(""#field1"").val(""Field 1 default value"");
$(""#field1"").trigger(""input"");
$(""#field2"").val(""Field 2 default value"");
$(""#field2"").trigger(""input"");

When I print out the filter values in my custom filter directive, all I see is field 1.  I tried removing the field1 trigger statement but then all I see is the field2 data and field1 disappears from the input box.  I saw posts about st-persist but I don't think the version I'm using contains that feature (and upgrading is not possible due to the lengthy approval process needed to install new software on our system).  Also, I'm not wanting the search filters to persist, just be able to initialize them.

How can I get around this problem?  I looked into trying to chain the trigger events but that didn't work.  Basically I would just like a way to initially set the search predicate field used in the smart-table code (the jQuery .val() will display the value and I was only using the .trigger() to force the filtering).

Thank you for the assistance.
",{},{}
