5577,IssuesEvent,2018-07-05 06:36:14+00:00,28647308,sjkingo/python-freshdesk,476440,sjkingo,,,closed,`FreshdeskModel._keys` set is shared between different submodels,"[{'id': 161961921, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWwxNjE5NjE5MjE=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/sjkingo/python-freshdesk/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'sjkingo', 'id': 476440, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjQ3NjQ0MA==', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/476440?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sjkingo', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/sjkingo', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sjkingo/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sjkingo/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sjkingo/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sjkingo/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sjkingo/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sjkingo/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sjkingo/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sjkingo/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sjkingo/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",1,"In the code there is a base class `FreshdeskModel` and submodels like `Ticket` or `Group` etc. In the base class the keys from JSON are stored into `_keys` set, but the problem is that this set is shared on base class level, i.e. singleton. So whenever you work with multiple models and access the `_keys` collection it will contain all keys from all models.

Steps to reproduce (example):
1) Query for ticket(s)
2) Query for contact(s)
3) Access `_keys` collection from any of the models
=> it contains keys from both tickets and contact
",{},{}
