6011,IssuesEvent,2016-07-17 18:30:39+00:00,38095954,eternnoir/pyTelegramBotAPI,1787385,AndydeCleyre,,,closed,"InlineQuery instance should provide a location attribute, if /setinlinegeo is enabled",[],[],1,"Hi,

Through BotFather, one can /setinlinegeo to enabled for a bot. Then, a user either grants or denies permission for the bot to access their location whenever they send a message to it.

If it is enabled, and the user grants permission, the `InlineQuery` instance should provide a `location` attribute.

From the [API docs](https://core.telegram.org/bots/api#inlinequery):

Field | Type | Description
----- | ---- | -----------
location | Location | *Optional.* Sender location, only for bots that request user location",{},{}
