6092,IssuesEvent,2018-03-21 14:30:36+00:00,122775780,kennethreitz/requests-html,1674433,beda42,,,opened,Encoding problem when HTML contains XML declaration,[],[],0,"Hi,

when a HTML (probably XHTML) contains an XML declaration with encoding (<?xml version=""1.0"" encoding=""UTF-8"" ?>), such as https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/CS/TXT/?qid=1521635262504&uri=CELEX:32008L0058, then working with the document crashes with

> ValueError: Unicode strings with encoding declaration are not supported. Please use bytes input or XML fragments without declaration.

in the lxml library. The problem is that lxml does not support already decoded unicode objects when there is encoding specified inside the document.

The fix would be to use `BaseParser.raw_html` instead of `BaseParser.html` when passing the content to `fromstring` in this case.

If you need any more details, please let me know.
Cheers
Beda

",{},{}
