7091,IssuesEvent,2018-02-11 04:06:54+00:00,34864402,apache/incubator-mxnet,1146226,nicklhy,47359,apache,opened,Too many header files need to be included when using C++ api,[],[],0,"Hi everyone, I am working on a C++ project which needs to use mxnet for CNN inference. I set `USE_CPP_PACKAGE = 1` and compiled mxnet source code myself.

In my C++ program, I only include `cpp-package/include/mxnet-cpp/MxNetCpp.h` at first but got errors like below:
```
/path/to/incubator-mxnet/cpp-package/include/mxnet-cpp/base.h:31:25: fatal error: mxnet/c_api.h: No such file or directory
```

It is caused by [`cpp-package/include/mxnet-cpp/base.h`](https://github.com/apache/incubator-mxnet/blob/master/cpp-package/include/mxnet-cpp/base.h#L31) which includes `mxnet/c_api.h` and `nnvm/c_api.h` inside it.
```
#include ""mxnet/c_api.h""
#include ""nnvm/c_api.h""
```
Thus, I have to add a lot more dirs to avoid the similar errors:
```
INCLUDE_DIRECTORIES(
    /path/to/incubator-mxnet/cpp-package/include
    /path/to/incubator-mxnet/include
    /path/to/incubator-mxnet/nnvm/include
    /path/to/incubator-mxnet/dmlc-core/include
    )
```

Just want to ask if it is possible to make the mxnet C++ api easier to use?

For instance, the mxnet cpp package folder only contains:
* `include`: all header files necessary for C++ development;
* `lib`: all libraries necessary for C++ development (i.e. libmxnet.so);",{},{}
