7369,IssuesEvent,2015-10-24 15:49:22+00:00,6930489,facebook/watchman,28623,DRMacIver,69631,facebook,opened,Off by one error in _int_size,[],[],0,"I noticed this when I was in the area from #179, but the \_int_size calculations have an off by one error: The smallest representable twos-complement integer in n bytes is -2^(n - 1), but this function treats it as if it were  - 2^(n - 1) - 1 (i.e. the negation of the largest reprsentable number).

This means that some numbers require one more byte to represent than is necessary (not a major deal) but also that it errors erroneously about -2^63.",{},{}
