7597,IssuesEvent,2018-01-19 18:43:17+00:00,525316,mozilla/bleach,352067,inducer,131524,mozilla,opened,Prevent unconditional sanitization of HTML attributes,[],[],0,"I'm following up from #346 (closed), which covered my need of letting some (but not all) `data:` URLs in `src` attributes pass the sanitizer. What that PR did was piggyback on attribute filters to determine when a value should be allowed to bypass [this logc](https://github.com/mozilla/bleach/blob/8706b5373b633407e804b1b2975edf8760067ff7/bleach/sanitizer.py#L511-L549) that is otherwise unconditionally applied.

In that PR, @willkg said:

> I suspect you can achieve what you're trying to achieve without making a substantial behavior change to Bleach.

Unless `data:` is added to the `allowed_protocols` (which seems risky), I don't see how this could be accomplished, but I would be happy to be educated.",{},{}
7601,IssuesEvent,2016-12-29 14:46:39+00:00,60273704,mozilla/DeepSpeech,12054740,kdavis-mozilla,131524,mozilla,opened,Dropout is too low,[],[],0,"From the last run at epoch 19 we had a training WER of 13.0%.

However, at epoch 19 we also had a validation WER of 56.6%.

The gulf between the two is far too large. Thus, the dropout rate should be increased.

The original deep speech paper used a dropout range from 5-10%. We are currently at 5%.

**So, we should try 10% to get a feel for how the upper limit behaves.**

**We should also check the validation and training WER every 10 epochs to monitor.**",{},{}
