8177,IssuesEvent,2015-12-23 20:25:29+00:00,24774658,boto/boto3,3434591,mattjacobus,327752,boto,opened,Creating apigateway integration request from boto3,[],[],0,"Hello,

I'm having trouble creating an apigateway integration from boto3.  When I call:
```python
c.put_integration(restApiId='zzz', resourceId='zzz', httpMethod='POST', integrationHttpMethod='POST', type='AWS', uri='uri')
```
I get:
```
KeyError: u'http_method'
```

Similarly when I use the cli I get:
```shell
aws apigateway put-integration --rest-api-id zzz --resource-id zzz --http-method POST --type AWS --uri uri
```
I get:
```
u'http_method'
```

If I add integrationHttpMethod='POST' to the boto3 call or --integration-http-method POST to the cli call as per the comments in [this issue](https://github.com/boto/boto3/issues/340), I get:
```
ParamValidationError: Parameter validation failed:
Unknown parameter in input: ""integrationHttpMethod"", must be one of: restApiId, resourceId, httpMethod, type, uri, credentials, requestParameters, requestTemplates, cacheNamespace, cacheKeyParameters
```

Any idea what I'm doing wrong?  If this is a bug, is there a workaround?
Thanks!",{},{}
