",{},{}
8184,IssuesEvent,2017-07-20 01:10:11+00:00,6670942,boto/botocore,703870,timuralp,327752,boto,opened,A urllib3 connection is not put back in the pool after HEAD,[],[],0,"Issuing a HEAD request results in the connection not being put back into the urllib3 pool. This is tied to this issue in urllib3: https://github.com/shazow/urllib3/issues/673. The problem is resolved in urllib3 >= 1.11. However, botocore vendors requests 2.7.0, which vendors urllib3 1.10.4. Updating the vendored requests library to >= 2.8.0 would resolve this issue.",{},{}
8187,IssuesEvent,2017-12-20 00:49:06+00:00,6670942,boto/botocore,1935727,joguSD,327752,boto,closed,Please add eu-west-3 to the list of available regions,[],[],1,"When calling `get_available_regions('ec2')` in `session.py`, _eu-west-3_ is not contained in the list of available regions that gets returned. However, the region is contained in line 607 of `endpoints.json`.

I believe the region not being returned is due to the fact that the _eu-west-3_ region is missing in the `regions` section (lines 12 to 55) of `endpoints.json`. This causes the check in line 114 of `regions.py` to evaluate to `False` and exclude the region from the list of regions that eventually gets returned.

Adding
```
""eu-west-3"" : {
  ""description"" : ""EU (Paris)""
}
```
to the aforementioned `regions` section (lines 12 to 55) of `endpoints.json` should fix the bug.",{},{}
