8400,IssuesEvent,2017-08-25 14:34:11+00:00,8649830,paypal/PayPal-Python-SDK,6819909,pp-randy,476675,paypal,closed,Constat 500 Internal Server Error when using the Payouts API,[],[],2,"### General information

* SDK/Library version: 1.13.1
* Environment: sandbox
* `PayPal-Debug-ID` values: c1932bd0c106d, 39ed501928fc4
* Language, language version, and OS: python 2.7.11 on Ubuntu 14.10

### Issue description
Hey! I'm trying to create a batch payout in sandbox, using only one recipient. The payload i'm using for the Payout object looks like this:
`{
   'items':[
      {
         'note':'Thank You!',
         'amount':{
            'currency':'USD',
            'value':'0.99'
         },
         'sender_item_id':'201403140002',
         'recipient_type':'EMAIL',
         'receiver':'x@x.eu'
      }
   ],
   'sender_batch_header':{
      'email_subject':'You have a payment from X!',
      'sender_batch_id':'ATZBZEGEIOMT'
   }
}`

Constantly getting 500 Internal Server Error with the following message:
`{
   ""name"":""INTERNAL_ERROR"",
   ""message"":""An internal service error has occurred."",
   ""debug_id"":""d2f960dd11018"",
   ""information_link"":""https://developer.paypal.com/docs/api/payments.payouts-batch/#errors""
}`",{},{}
8402,IssuesEvent,2016-10-04 03:11:13+00:00,8649830,paypal/PayPal-Python-SDK,3358986,braebot,476675,paypal,closed,Is there a way to use parallel payments in python-sdk?,[],[],1,"Hello,

