8930,IssuesEvent,2016-06-16 03:57:44+00:00,12710059,edoburu/django-parler,3462279,sunjoomoon,738973,edoburu,closed,mptt admin indent issue,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/edoburu/django-parler/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}]",[],5,"Following http://django-parler.readthedocs.org/en/latest/advanced/mptt.html#integration-with-django-mptt, all seems okay but with below in admin.py

1) without ```list_display``` as below, title indent is okay. 
```
from django.contrib import admin
from parler.admin import TranslatableAdmin, TranslatableModelForm
from mptt.admin import MPTTModelAdmin
from mptt.forms import MPTTAdminForm
from .models import Category


class CategoryAdminForm(MPTTAdminForm, TranslatableModelForm):
    pass


class CategoryAdmin(TranslatableAdmin, MPTTModelAdmin):
    form = CategoryAdminForm

    def get_prepopulated_fields(self, request, obj=None):
        return {'slug': ('title',)}  # needed for translated fields


admin.site.register(Category, CategoryAdmin)
```

2) BUT if  ```list_display``` is used, then somehow second column value is indented. In this case, ```is_published``` is indented.
```
from django.contrib import admin
from parler.admin import TranslatableAdmin, TranslatableModelForm
from mptt.admin import MPTTModelAdmin
from mptt.forms import MPTTAdminForm
from .models import Category


class CategoryAdminForm(MPTTAdminForm, TranslatableModelForm):
    pass


class CategoryAdmin(TranslatableAdmin, MPTTModelAdmin):
    form = CategoryAdminForm
   ** list_display = ('title','is_published','order','language_column',)**

    def get_prepopulated_fields(self, request, obj=None):
        return {'slug': ('title',)}  # needed for translated fields


admin.site.register(Category, CategoryAdmin)
```

What am I missing?",{},{}
