8961,IssuesEvent,2015-10-12 14:55:05+00:00,4978045,Parsely/pykafka,723615,emmett9001,779641,Parsely,closed,Cluster does not reconnect to disconnected brokers,[],[],3,"Behaviour: a KafkaClient cluster does not reconnect to disconnected brokers that have become available again.

Test environment: a 3 broker Kafka cluster with a replication factor of 2 on the test topic.

To reproduce:
* Connect a producer to the cluster and produce messages continuously.
* The producer connects to 2 out of 3 brokers in the cluster, since the replication factor is 2. For this example, let's say we are connected to brokers 1 and 2, but not to broker 3.
* Stop broker 1.
* The producer notices the disconnect and updates the leader from 1 to 2 or 3 on some of its partitions.
* Everything keeps running smoothly.
* Start broker 1 again.
* Everything keeps running smoothly.
* Stop broker 2.
* The producer notices the disconnect and updates the leader from 2 to 1 or 3 on some of its partitions.
* The producer never tried to reconnect to broker 1, so sending messages fails.
* After 3 retries, the producer dies with an exception.

Error output:
```
2015-10-09 15:29:33,445 ERROR Exception encountered in worker thread:
  File ""/workspace/pykafka/pykafka/producer.py"", line 403, in queue_reader
    self.producer._send_request(batch, self)
  File ""/workspace/pykafka/pykafka/producer.py"", line 351, in _send_request
    ""retries."", self._max_retries)

2015-10-09 15:29:33,448 INFO Blocking until all messages are sent
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""produce-pykafka.py"", line 46, in <module>
    break
  File ""/workspace/pykafka/pykafka/producer.py"", line 169, in __exit__
    self.stop()
  File ""/workspace/pykafka/pykafka/producer.py"", line 219, in stop
    self._wait_all()
  File ""/workspace/pykafka/pykafka/producer.py"", line 363, in _wait_all
    self._raise_worker_exceptions()
  File ""/workspace/pykafka/pykafka/producer.py"", line 154, in _raise_worker_exceptions
    raise ex
pykafka.exceptions.ProduceFailureError: ('Message failed to send after %d retries.', 3)
```

Proposed fix: Try to reconnect to all available brokers on a call to cluster.update(). Some connections might fail, but just leave those disconnected until the next call to update().
",{},{}
8970,IssuesEvent,2016-03-10 05:46:09+00:00,4978045,Parsely/pykafka,655305,lucidfrontier45,779641,Parsely,opened,Identical KafkaClient is created in different process,[],[],0,"Hi all. I'm working on Simple Task worker that contains a Kafka consumer.
My code is as follows.

```python
om multiprocessing import Process

from pykafka import KafkaClient


class KafkaWorker(Process):
    def __init__(self):
        Process.__init__(self)

    def run(self):
        print(""{} start"".format(self.pid))

        c = KafkaClient(hosts=""127.0.0.1:9091"")
        print(""{}'s client id = {}"".format(self.pid, id(c)))
        topic = c.topics[""test""]
        consumer = topic.get_balanced_consumer(consumer_group='testgroup',
                                               auto_commit_enable=True,
                                               zookeeper_connect=""127.0.0.1:2281"")
        for msg in consumer:
            print(self.pid, msg.value)


w1 = KafkaWorker()
w1.start()
w2 = KafkaWorker()
w2.start()
```
When I run this code, it says

```python
13452 start
13453 start
13452's client id = 139805036298320
13453's client id = 139805036298320
No handlers could be found for logger ""pykafka.balancedconsumer""
Process KafkaWorker-2:
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/multiprocessing/process.py"", line 258, in _bootstrap
    self.run()
  File ""/home/du/PycharmProjects/BusyBee/examples/kafka_test.py"", line 19, in run
    for msg in consumer:
  File ""/home/du/.virtualenvs/busybee/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/pykafka/balancedconsumer.py"", line 722, in __iter__
    message = self.consume(block=True)
  File ""/home/du/.virtualenvs/busybee/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/pykafka/balancedconsumer.py"", line 711, in consume
    raise ConsumerStoppedException
ConsumerStoppedException
```
You can see the two KafkaClient instances have the same id and one of the consumers gives `ConsumerStoppedException`.

What is the right way to include KafkaClient in a Process?  

**Python version**: 2.7,
**PyKafka version**: 2.2.1
**Kafka version**: 0.9.0.1""
",{},{}
8977,IssuesEvent,2015-06-21 06:25:04+00:00,4978045,Parsely/pykafka,694341,zhynxn,779641,Parsely,opened,how to manually set offset,[],[],0,"Hello, 
I have question about set offset for consumer-group on partition. 
I know there is auto_offset_reset parameter to reset the offset to LATEST or EARLIEST when OffsetOutOfRangeError happens. It is really helpful. 

My question is can I manually set specific offset number for consumer-group, partition? So I can do more error handling in my own program. 

There is such function in kafka-python package (http://kafka-python.readthedocs.org/en/latest/apidoc/kafka.consumer.html) 

Please let me know. 
Thanks,
Yanxin 


set_topic_partitions(*topics)
Set the topic/partitions to consume Optionally specify offsets to start from

Accepts types:

str (utf-8): topic name (will consume all available partitions)
tuple: (topic, partition)
dict:
{ topic: partition }
{ topic: [partition list] }
{ topic: (partition tuple,) }
Optionally, offsets can be specified directly:

tuple: (topic, partition, offset)
dict: { (topic, partition): offset, ... }
",{},{}
