9141,IssuesEvent,2016-12-16 20:07:40+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,704995,gongzhitaao,897180,scikit-image,opened,API resize/rescale redundant?,[],[],0,"## Description
Any difference between the two API, [rescale](http://scikit-image.org/docs/stable/api/skimage.transform.html#rescale) vs [resize](http://scikit-image.org/docs/stable/api/skimage.transform.html#resize)?  It seems to me having both is redundant and confusing.  And as for code, `rescale` is just a thin wrapper around `resize`.

",{},{}
9170,IssuesEvent,2018-06-27 21:12:56+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,40644331,jpcornil-git,897180,scikit-image,opened,Inccorect inertia_tensor implementation,[],[],0,"## Description
Implementation of inertia_tensor in skimage/measure/_moments.py is not correct

Diagonal components of inertia_tensor are currently set to second order moments  (e.g. m[2,0,0] for Ixx in a 3D system) but they should be set to the sum of all 2nd order moments but the one for the corresponding axe (i.e. sum of square of the distance from corresponding axe).

`teste
tes`",{},{}
9204,IssuesEvent,2018-07-22 19:41:49+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,29165011,kne42,897180,scikit-image,opened,Standardize argument broadcasting,[],[],0,"We should standardize cases in which arguments that require a list/tuple/iterable of values can also accept a singular value which is broadcast to the same shape. For example, `42 -> (42, 42, 42)`.

> @soupault wrote in https://github.com/scikit-image/scikit-image/pull/2747#issuecomment-389236345:
> ... I'd suggest to converge on a codestyle for handling such cases (I can see that they appear quite often), so that we do not check for `if not isinstance(sigma, coll.Iterable)` in one place and `if type(center) not in [tuple, list, np.ndarray]` in another. As an option, by pre-casting the parameter to ndarray, and then checking what is needed in a unified way.
",{},{}
