9315,IssuesEvent,2016-12-17 22:37:40+00:00,16366081,numenta/nupic.core,364113,mrcslws,1039191,numenta,opened,SparseMatrix methods copy their inputs,[],[],0,"Every single `NumpyVectorT` in [sparse_matrix.i](https://github.com/numenta/nupic.core/blob/5055a73c0a9eb8d3c52051b7f023c75605fabed4/src/nupic/bindings/sparse_matrix.i) is allocating a new vector. So whenever we put the inputs into a NumpyVectorT, we're copying the values, even when the values are already in a numpy array with the correct dtype.

It appears this comment is incorrect: https://github.com/numenta/nupic.core/blob/5055a73c0a9eb8d3c52051b7f023c75605fabed4/src/nupic/py_support/NumpyVector.hpp#L167

When I remove this unnecessary copying for the SparseMatrix methods that we use, I get a nice speed boost.",{},{}
