9492,IssuesEvent,2017-10-16 11:52:57+00:00,37462194,inveniosoftware/invenio-records,4287772,drjova,1157480,inveniosoftware,closed,RFC: moving json column to jsonb,[],[],7,"Proposal
======

Move `RecordMetadata` json column to `JSONB` when using `postgresql`.

The following code:

```
json = db.Column(
        JSONType().with_variant(
            postgresql.JSON(none_as_null=True),
            'postgresql',
        ),
        default=lambda: dict(),
        nullable=True
    )
```

Can be converted to

```

json = db.Column(
        db.JSON().with_variant(
            postgresql.JSONB(none_as_null=True),
            'postgresql',
        ),
        default=lambda: dict(),
        nullable=True
    )
```

This will allow to use native `jsonb` column in PostgreSQL (see https://www.postgresql.org/docs/9.4/static/datatype-json.html) with advantages such as better indexing capabilities and using containment operators.

-----------

I have tested locally with `PostgreSQL v9.5` and:

```
Flask-SQLAlchemy==2.2
SQLAlchemy==1.1.10
SQLAlchemy-Continuum==1.3.0
SQLAlchemy-Utils==0.32.14
```

And everything seems to work as expected, enabling queries such as:

```
db.session.query(RecordMetadata).filter(type_coerce(RecordMetadata.json, JSONB()).contains({""control_number"": 1498185})).all()
```

(Note that `type_coerce` is needed because of the `with_variant` construct - [more info](https://bitbucket.org/zzzeek/sqlalchemy/issues/3855/comparator-on-variant-field)

Which translates to:

```
SELECT *
FROM records_metadata
WHERE records_metadata.json @> '{""control_number"": 1498185}'
```

----------------------------

The only thing missing to be done is to write an Alembic recipe to migrate the column.

cc @lnielsen 

Related to https://github.com/inveniosoftware/invenio-db/issues/19",{},{}
9496,IssuesEvent,2017-05-10 15:11:46+00:00,35280261,inveniosoftware/invenio-accounts,5708796,nharraud,1157480,inveniosoftware,closed,global: logout_listener fails when using logout_user,"[{'id': 414883496, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio-accounts/labels/Size:%20easy', 'name': 'Size: easy', 'color': 'bc3cbc', 'default': False}, {'id': 267624676, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio-accounts/labels/Status:%20in%20review', 'name': 'Status: in review', 'color': '3cbc3c', 'default': False}, {'id': 209124211, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio-accounts/labels/Type:%20bug', 'name': 'Type: bug', 'color': 'ff2a00', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'nharraud', 'id': 5708796, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/5708796?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/nharraud', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",2,"**Problem:**
Using `logout_user()` after calling `login_user(user)` in tests will fail. This happens because they are used in a `test_request_context` and, as [explained in flask documentation](http://flask.pocoo.org/docs/0.12/testing/#other-testing-tricks)

*""the `before_request()` and `after_request()` functions are not called automatically.""*

As [`login_listener`](https://github.com/inveniosoftware/invenio-accounts/blob/559284550f4b6f2fa964f11be27fc269489dbf43/invenio_accounts/sessions.py#L58)creates the session after the request, using `@flask.after_this_request`, the session is not created when calling `login_user(user)`. However  [`logout_listener`](https://github.com/inveniosoftware/invenio-accounts/blob/559284550f4b6f2fa964f11be27fc269489dbf43/invenio_accounts/sessions.py#L79) deletes the session immediately instead of also doing it in `@flask.after_this_request`, which fails as the session does not exist.

**Suggested solution:**
Moving the code [deleting the session](https://github.com/inveniosoftware/invenio-accounts/blob/559284550f4b6f2fa964f11be27fc269489dbf43/invenio_accounts/sessions.py#L85-L87) in the [after request function](https://github.com/inveniosoftware/invenio-accounts/blob/559284550f4b6f2fa964f11be27fc269489dbf43/invenio_accounts/sessions.py#L89).

@lnielsen Do you see any issue with the suggested solution. All the tests in invenio-accounts and invenio-oauthclient seem to pass when I do this.",{},{}
