10772,IssuesEvent,2017-03-02 10:51:06+00:00,15510373,openfisca/openfisca-web-api,222463,MattiSG,1794404,openfisca,closed,Design new calculate endpoint,[],"[{'login': 'cbenz', 'id': 12686, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/12686?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/cbenz', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/cbenz', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/cbenz/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/cbenz/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/cbenz/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/cbenz/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/cbenz/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/cbenz/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/cbenz/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/cbenz/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/cbenz/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",5,"Create a new endpoint merging existing `calculate` and `simulate` endpoint. This would be the version 2 of `calculate` so let's name it `/api/2/calculate`.

Here are some constraints:
- the Web API must remain stateless (no session on the server)
- the JSON payload brings the calculate request
## Input

The new endpoint should be able to accept multiple formats in input:
- test case
- arrays

Options
- `simple_test_case`: allow a test case to be incomplete
## Output

The output format should be either:
- test case
- arrays

Some feature are already provided by `calculate` or `simulate`. The aim of the new endpoint is to unify them in a consistent manner.
## Examples

