11324,IssuesEvent,2017-07-24 13:42:07+00:00,16316451,GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python,675151,evanj,2810941,GoogleCloudPlatform,closed,google-cloud-datastore: Import fails with latest setuptools 36.2.1,[],[],2,"Creating a new virtualenv that uses the latest version of setuptools fails to correctly install google-cloud-datastore. Using it will fail with `ImportError: No module named proto.datastore.v1`. The reason seems to be that the package `gapic-google-cloud-datastore-v1` depends on `proto-google-cloud-datastore-v1[grpc]<0.91dev,>=0.90.3`. I believe the `[grpc]` part causes the new versions of setuptools to consider this an ""extra"" dependency and not include it.

The workaround is to explicitly install this package in `requirements.txt`, but either `google-cloud-datastore` or `gapic-google-cloud-datastore-v1` should have its dependencies fixed so this works

