11762,IssuesEvent,2017-09-15 22:56:17+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,46740,stuhood,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,soft-excludes not applied at compile time,[],[],0,"[stuhood/soft-excludes-compilation](https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/compare/master...twitter:stuhood/soft-excludes-compilation) contains an example of a target that fails to compile with `--no-resolve-ivy-soft-excludes`, but succeeds with `--resolve-ivy-soft-excludes`.

The exclude should definitely still apply to compilation with `soft-excludes` (as all of the necessary graph information is present), but with or without strict_deps, the excludes are not applied. Most likely this is just an oversight in the classpath calculations here: https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/blob/master/src/python/pants/backend/jvm/tasks/jvm_compile/jvm_compile.py#L879

(relates to #4437)",{},{}
