11832,IssuesEvent,2016-11-18 16:50:42+00:00,25538034,awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client-python,18317277,pfifer,3299148,awslabs,closed,Pip install from cache does not include KCL jars,"[{'id': 140065633, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client-python/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'pfifer', 'id': 18317277, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/18317277?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pfifer', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/pfifer', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pfifer/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pfifer/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pfifer/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pfifer/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pfifer/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pfifer/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pfifer/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pfifer/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pfifer/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",7,"We noticed that after the recent changes (fix of #28) the `amazon_kclpy` package has a bug regarding downloads of JAR files.

Steps to reproduce:

```
$ cd /tmp
$ virtualenv .venv
$ . .venv/bin/activate
$ pip install --no-cache amazon_kclpy
$ ls .venv/lib/python*/site-packages/amazon_kclpy/jars
__init__.py amazon-kinesis-client-1.7.2.jar aws-java-sdk-cloudwatch-1.11.14.jar ...
$ pip uninstall -y amazon_kclpy
$ pip install amazon_kclpy
$ ls .venv/lib/python*/site-packages/amazon_kclpy/jars
__init__.py
```

After the last step, the JAR files are missing in the `jars` directory. Would be great to get this fixed because most people will probably not use the `--no-cache` option on `pip install`, then the library becomes unusable.",{},{}
11838,IssuesEvent,2018-01-10 19:59:28+00:00,70530854,awslabs/serverless-application-model,22755571,sanathkr,3299148,awslabs,closed,Add Debugging Guide,"[{'id': 797198210, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/awslabs/serverless-application-model/labels/area/troubleshooting', 'name': 'area/troubleshooting', 'color': 'b60205', 'default': False}, {'id': 797198219, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/awslabs/serverless-application-model/labels/type/documentation', 'name': 'type/documentation', 'color': '0e8a16', 'default': False}]",[],2,People [often ask](https://github.com/awslabs/serverless-application-model/issues/20#issuecomment-270496029) about how to debug SAM templates. Add a DEBUGGING guide them through,{},{}
11843,IssuesEvent,2017-02-06 23:21:59+00:00,70530854,awslabs/serverless-application-model,1107818,madmod,3299148,awslabs,opened,Policy not applied,[],[],0,"When I create a lambda with a statement like the following the policy is not applied but no error is thrown either. The result is a policy with only the `AWSLambdaBasicExecutionRole` without any Role policies.

```yaml
  SignAttachmentUploadFunction:
    Type: 'AWS::Serverless::Function'
    Properties:
      Handler: 'index.handler'
      Runtime: 'nodejs4.3'
      CodeUri: 'lambdas/sign-attachment-upload'
      Description: !Sub '${Project} API endpoint for signing a new file upload with a random filename hash.'
      Policies:
        - PolicyName: 'AllowAttachmentUploads'
          PolicyDocument:
            Version: '2012-10-17'
            Statement:
              - Effect: 'Allow'
                Action:
                  - 's3:PutObject'
                  - 's3:PutObjectACL'
                Resource: !Sub 'arn:aws:s3:::${AttachmentsBucket}/*'
      Environment:
        Variables:
          AttachmentUploadBucket: !Ref 'AttachmentsBucket'
      Events:
        SignAttachmentUpload:
          Type: 'Api'
          Properties:
            Path: '/sign-attachment-upload'
            Method: 'post'
    DependsOn:
      - 'AttachmentsBucket'
```

I solved it by only including the `PolicyDocument` instead of the entire policy.

```yaml
  SignAttachmentUploadFunction:
    Type: 'AWS::Serverless::Function'
    Properties:
      Handler: 'index.handler'
      Runtime: 'nodejs4.3'
      CodeUri: 'lambdas/sign-attachment-upload'
      Description: !Sub '${Project} API endpoint for signing a new file upload with a random filename hash.'
      Policies:
        - Version: '2012-10-17'
          Statement:
            - Effect: 'Allow'
              Action:
                - 's3:PutObject'
                - 's3:PutObjectACL'
              Resource: !Sub 'arn:aws:s3:::${AttachmentsBucket}/*'
      Environment:
        Variables:
          AttachmentUploadBucket: !Ref 'AttachmentsBucket'
      Events:
        SignAttachmentUpload:
          Type: 'Api'
          Properties:
            Path: '/sign-attachment-upload'
            Method: 'post'
    DependsOn:
      - 'AttachmentsBucket'
```

Thanks!",{},{}
11844,IssuesEvent,2017-08-07 09:30:32+00:00,70530854,awslabs/serverless-application-model,7237082,felixbecker,3299148,awslabs,closed,Log Metric DependsOn - Lambda creation,[],[],0,"Hi, 

