11922,IssuesEvent,2018-06-13 19:09:32+00:00,9861437,imageio/imageio,3345836,mszegedy,3678179,imageio,opened,Clarify version of ffmpeg needed for video capabilities in anaconda distribution,[],[],0,"It would be helpful if the documentation explicitly recommended which ffmpeg package to install from Anaconda Cloud so that the primary video capabilities of imageio would work, in the case that one is installing imageio from there. For example, I had `anacoda/ffmpeg` lying around as my ffmpeg package, and found out that it's missing the libx264 codec for encoding H.264 video, which made imageio's video writers fail when having frames appended to them. It took me a while to realize that the problem was with my ffmpeg distribution, and that I should install `conda-forge/ffmpeg` instead.
The [current documentation](http://imageio.readthedocs.io/en/stable/installation.html) on installing imageio promises that imageio will ""help ... download"" additional libraries needed for various operations, but it wasn't very helpful here; the only helpful I ever got was ffmpeg saying `Unknown encoder 'libx264'`. An explicit list of optional dependencies and recommended sources for them on that page in particular would be helpful.",{},{}
