12066,IssuesEvent,2017-12-05 18:57:39+00:00,49976939,learningequality/kolibri,10248067,jonboiser,3926525,learningequality,opened,Style Guide - Provide guidance/examples on how to use in unit tests,"[{'id': 635590764, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/learningequality/kolibri/labels/TASK:%20style%20guide', 'name': 'TASK: style guide', 'color': '72486f', 'default': False}]",[],0,"### Observed behavior

In my experience, interacting with Keen-UI components (e.g. clicking, changing inputs, etc.) has forced me to use a different approach than with plain HTML elements. For example, to cause a behavior on an HTML element, I can simply do `el.trigger('click')`, whereas with the Vue component, I will sometimes need to reach into the component's view model and simulate an Event by calling a view model method directly (e.g. `component.vm.handleClickYes()`).

Whether this is correct from my (i.e. the test writer) perspective or the component author is up for debate, but it would be nice if there were code examples for each style guide element explaining how one would do basic testing if I were to use the component in the app.

### Expected behavior

Some suggestions for the style-guide

* **Interactivity** explain how to click/change/etc. the form element
* **assertions** how to make assertions on relevant part of the component or the bigger part of the app

",{},{}
