12215,IssuesEvent,2018-08-07 02:57:40+00:00,53143022,oduwsdl/ipwb,65147,ibnesayeed,4416806,oduwsdl,opened,Remote index argument is ambiguous,[],[],0,"Currently, the replay allows supplying:

1. no index (which is then replaced with a default local index file or read from the pipe)
2. a local file as index
3. an HTTP URI
4. an IPFS hash

The first case is being tracked under #426. However, I think we should use a proper IPFS scheme for the fourth case otherwise it is ambiguous with the local file names.

Better yet, we can completely remove the support of remote index files as they are not serving any advantage other than some convenience with the cost of complex logic and unnecessary maintenance overhead. Basically, remote index file is fetched initially and cached locally (which can be done by manually before starting the replay). If the replay was periodically fetching and synchronizing changes from the remote file to the local cache then it would be more useful (but that would be pointless as IPFS being a content-addressable file system would not have any updated content on the same hash, though the HTTP URIs could). Also, if the lookup was performed remotely using range header then it would have been useful (though, very slow). In summary, the benefit of supporting remote index for now is not worth the effort and complexity it brings.",{},{}
