12278,IssuesEvent,2017-08-05 12:34:09+00:00,11003251,acorg/dark-matter,132978,terrycojones,4853692,acorg,opened,Make it possible to remove duplicate sequences based on read id,"[{'id': 45358330, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/acorg/dark-matter/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'terrycojones', 'id': 132978, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/132978?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/terrycojones', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/terrycojones', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/terrycojones/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/terrycojones/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/terrycojones/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/terrycojones/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/terrycojones/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/terrycojones/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/terrycojones/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/terrycojones/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/terrycojones/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"The `--removeDuplicates` argument to `filter-fasta.py` only uses the read sequences to determine what is a duplicate. Using it can result in removing multiple distinct reads, which may not be what you want. Add a `--removeDuplicatesById` option to do the removing based just on read id. This is useful for cases where a set of reads is matched against a database using multiple methods and as a final step you need to remove duplicates based just on id.",{},{}
