13119,IssuesEvent,2016-09-30 16:59:14+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,7231234,jessehoff,6392739,conda,opened,Conda create from .yml,[],[],0,"When trying to share an environment using the steps provided on conda.pydata.org there is a simple problem; All libraries in the .yml are assumed to be from conda.anaconda (with my install). When using --explicit and providing the exact origin of the package (mostly stuff from bioconda) installation works, but this might not be as easy or robust. It should be otherwise possible to store the information about how conda knew where the package came from. 

