13343,IssuesEvent,2017-08-29 16:52:34+00:00,9801644,elastic/elasticsearch-py,32132,HonzaKral,6764390,elastic,closed,`indices.exists` is misleading with wildcard indices,[],[],1,"Since `indices.exists(ix)` is more or less defined to be `HEAD /ix == 20x`, `indices.exists(""*"")` always returns true, even if there are no indices. I see two sensible things to do here, maybe there are others?

1. change `indices.exists` to return `len(GET /ix)` (at least if wildcards are involved)
