13363,IssuesEvent,2017-06-02 18:25:04+00:00,64148806,Azure/blobxfer,7535975,alfpark,6844498,Azure,closed,Unable to upload large files,"[{'id': 413888719, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/blobxfer/labels/defect', 'name': 'defect', 'color': 'ee0701', 'default': False}, {'id': 413888721, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/blobxfer/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'alfpark', 'id': 7535975, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/7535975?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/alfpark', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/alfpark', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/alfpark/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/alfpark/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/alfpark/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/alfpark/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/alfpark/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/alfpark/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/alfpark/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/alfpark/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/alfpark/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",3,"I tried to use blobxfer to upload a large file (around 264 GB) to an azure block blob storage. The tool could not upload the file. The error message was:

> RuntimeError: 63084 chunks for file my_big_file exceeds Azure Storage limits for a single block blob

I believe that this is due to the limitation on the MAX_BLOB_CHUNK_SIZE_BYTES set to 4194304 (63084 * 4194304 B = 264 GB). According to [azure documentation](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/azure-subscription-service-limits#storage-limits), the maximum number of blocks in a block blob is 50000 blocks of 100 MB. 63084 blocks is of course over the limit for the number of blocks and that is why it fails. But I don't understand this artificial limitation to the maximum block size of 4194304 bytes (which is 4 MB) imposed by blobxfer, which is 25 times less than the maximum in the azure documentation.

Anyway, the quick fix for me was to increase the value of MAX_BLOB_CHUNK_SIZE_BYTES to a higher value and then I could upload my file without any issue.",{},{}
13369,IssuesEvent,2017-07-07 18:58:04+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,308610,jaraco,6844498,Azure,opened,Easier login experience,[],[],0,"### Description

Each time I enter `az login`, I then automatically take several actions:
- copy the code to the clipboard
- launch my default browser
- enter the URL into the browser

There's no reason the client couldn't do these three things for me, using [jaraco.clipboard](https://pypi.org/project/jaraco.clipboard/) or similar for clipboard functionality and other techniques for launching a browser. Or even better if the browser could be launched with the code in the URL, saving the paste action also.

I suspect such a feature should only be enabled opt-in (as parameters to `login` command).

Thoughts?

---

### Environment summary

**Install Method:** How did you install the CLI? (e.g. pip, interactive script, apt-get, Docker, MSI, nightly)  
Answer here: pip

**CLI Version:** What version of the CLI and modules are installed? (Use `az --version`)  
Answer here: 2.0.10 (though `az --version` fails due to another bug)

**OS Version:** What OS and version are you using?  
Answer here: macOS 10.12.5

**Shell Type:** What shell are you using? (e.g. bash, cmd.exe, Bash on Windows)  
Answer here: zsh

",{},{}
