13761,IssuesEvent,2018-05-22 20:52:47+00:00,13258039,aio-libs/aiohttp,356399,asvetlov,7049303,aio-libs,closed,Improve middleware documentation,"[{'id': 445958404, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/aio-libs/aiohttp/labels/docs%20/%20examples', 'name': 'docs / examples', 'color': 'd4c5f9', 'default': False}, {'id': 277836062, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/aio-libs/aiohttp/labels/easy', 'name': 'easy', 'color': 'fbca04', 'default': False}]",[],5,"Current docs are not exhausting clean (#2848 for example).

https://docs.aiohttp.org/en/stable/web_advanced.html#middlewares section should have an example for *middleware factory* (a function that creates a middleware with passed arguments).

*middleware factory* conflicts with a factory for old-style middlewares, I think dropping *old-styles* from docs is ok (but we should support this old style for a while, #2851)

Document that *normalize path middleware* https://docs.aiohttp.org/en/stable/web_reference.html#normalize-path-middleware is actually a factory.",{},{}
13762,IssuesEvent,2018-03-20 13:44:03+00:00,13258039,aio-libs/aiohttp,598990,fafhrd91,7049303,aio-libs,closed,Session objects / connection pulls are worthless,"[{'id': 58986080, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/aio-libs/aiohttp/labels/wontfix', 'name': 'wontfix', 'color': 'b7942c', 'default': True}]",[],1,"## Long story short

<!-- Please describe your problem and why the fix is important. -->

Most realistic webservers don't act the way you may imagine, so, in practice, every request in this library made through session object ends up invalidating this session.  So, not only session object introduces a lot of complication (one would need to use some sort of mutual exclusion to ensure single session object is created to deal with multiple requests), but it also doesn't do what it's supposed to: on every server I've tried so far, after every request, successful or not, I get `aiohttp.client_exceptions.ServerDisconnectedError`.

## Expected behaviour

<!-- What is the behaviour you expect? -->

Just deal with life the way it is.  The problems your library has with maintaining connection pull need to be swept under your carpet. They are absolutely of no interest to your users.

## Actual behaviour

<!-- What's actually happening? -->

Tons of meaningless exceptions which require a lot of intricate handling with zero benefit to the user.

## Steps to reproduce

<!-- Please describe steps to reproduce the issue.
     If you have a script that does that please include it here within
     markdown code markup -->

Write any code that reuses session object, run it through some arbitrary selection of sites and see how often you get server disconnect errors.

## Your environment

<!-- Describe the environment you have that lead to your issue.
     This includes aiohttp version, OS, proxy server and other bits that
     are related to your case. 
     
     IMPORTANT: aiohttp is both server framework and client library.
     For getting rid of confusing please put 'server', 'client' or 'both'
     word here.
     -->

Unimportant.",{},{}
