14403,IssuesEvent,2018-02-12 13:54:33+00:00,39858489,juju-solutions/charms.reactive,406082,johnsca,8684561,juju-solutions,closed,joined flag only removed in the hook after the relation-broken hook,[],"[{'login': 'johnsca', 'id': 406082, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/406082?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johnsca', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/johnsca', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johnsca/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johnsca/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johnsca/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johnsca/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johnsca/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johnsca/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johnsca/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johnsca/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johnsca/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",11,"The docs say the following

> the `joined` flag will be automatically cleared when there are no remote units remaining on any relation, but neither of the other flags will be automatically cleared.

I read this as ""the `joined` flag will be removed **when the last unit of the last relationship is `departed`**"". So for an endpoint with one relation and one remote unit, the `joined` flag will be removed at the same time that the `departed` flag is set.

This is however not the case: the `joined` flag is only removed when during the hook _after_ the  `relation-broken` hook because that is the first time when Juju says that there are no relations/units connected anymore.

Look at this output. The desired behavior is that the `joined` flag is removed in the first `departed` hook, not in the `update-status` hook.

``` bash
# Departed hook
2018-01-18 13:16:30 INFO juju-log kubernetes-request:94: Reactive main running for hook kubernetes-request-relation-departed
2018-01-18 13:16:31 INFO juju-log kubernetes-request:94: Invoking reactive handler: reactive/kubernetes-resource.py:11:print_flags
2018-01-18 13:16:31 INFO juju-log kubernetes-request:94: [
  'endpoint.kubernetes-request.changed', 
  'endpoint.kubernetes-request.changed.egress-subnets', 
  'endpoint.kubernetes-request.changed.ingress-address', 
  'endpoint.kubernetes-request.changed.private-address', 
  'endpoint.kubernetes-request.departed', 
  'endpoint.kubernetes-request.joined', 
  'kubernetes.connected']

# Broken hook
2018-01-18 13:16:32 INFO juju-log kubernetes-request:94: Reactive main running for hook kubernetes-request-relation-broken
2018-01-18 13:16:32 INFO juju-log kubernetes-request:94: Invoking reactive handler: reactive/kubernetes-resource.py:11:print_flags
2018-01-18 13:16:32 INFO juju-log kubernetes-request:94: [
  'endpoint.kubernetes-request.changed', 
  'endpoint.kubernetes-request.changed.egress-subnets', 
  'endpoint.kubernetes-request.changed.ingress-address', 
  'endpoint.kubernetes-request.changed.private-address', 
  'endpoint.kubernetes-request.departed', 
  'endpoint.kubernetes-request.joined', 
  'kubernetes.connected']

# Update status hook
2018-01-18 13:21:27 INFO juju-log Reactive main running for hook update-status
2018-01-18 13:21:27 INFO juju-log Invoking reactive handler: reactive/kubernetes-resource.py:16:k8s_resource_install
2018-01-18 13:21:27 INFO juju-log NO DEPLOYER RELATION
2018-01-18 13:21:27 INFO juju-log Invoking reactive handler: reactive/kubernetes-resource.py:11:print_flags
2018-01-18 13:21:28 INFO juju-log [
  'endpoint.kubernetes-request.changed',
  'endpoint.kubernetes-request.changed.egress-subnets',
  'endpoint.kubernetes-request.changed.ingress-address',
  'endpoint.kubernetes-request.changed.private-address',
  'endpoint.kubernetes-request.departed']
```

This behavior requires a developer to know the intricacies of when Juju stops saying there is a relationship.

I propose we remove the `joined` flag, during the `departed` hook of the last unit of the last relationship.

1. It's more intuitive,
2. it's how it's explained in the docs,
3. and the current behavior serves no purpose, afaik.

What do you think, @johnsca ?",{},{}
