14700,IssuesEvent,2017-07-18 15:06:32+00:00,26784827,dotnet/core,28010173,leilasoriano,9141961,dotnet,opened,.NET Core plus Angular 2: receiving null on file parameter,[],[],0,"Hi,

I'm using .NETCore 1.1 and Angular 2. My code is below:

NET Core Web API backend

```
    [HttpPost(""[Action]"")]
            public async Task<Documento> UploadArquivo([FromForm]IFormFile arquivo)
            {}
```

Angular front

Service:
```
uploadArquivo(arquivoParaUpload: any) {
        let input = new FormData();
        input.append('arquivo', arquivoParaUpload);

     return this.requisicaoService.http.post(this.requisicaoService.urlBase + '/proposta/uploadArquivo', input, this.requisicaoService.merge(options))
          .map(response => response.json())
              .catch(this.errorHandler);
    }
```

Component:

```
uploadArquivo(): void {
    let fi = this.inputArquivo.nativeElement;

    if (fi.files && fi.files[0]) {
        let arquivo = fi.files[0];
        this.propostaService
            .uploadArquivo(arquivo)
            .subscribe(res => {
                console.log(res);
            });
    }
}
```
Html:

```
<input #InputArquivo type=""file"" class=""form-control mb-2 mr-sm-2 mb-sm-0 input-file-Upload"" name = ""arquivo"" (change)=""uploadArquivo()"">
      <span class=""col""></span>
      <button type=""submit"" class=""btn btn-primary""  (click)=""uploadArquivo()"">Upload do documento</button>
```

I'm receiving always value null on controller method. I tried several solutions, but nothing works for me.

Thanks in advance!",{},{}
