14722,IssuesEvent,2017-06-29 00:48:37+00:00,26784827,dotnet/core,19564268,olivd,9141961,dotnet,closed,Unit tests in 1.04 no longer running (xunit),[],[],7,"Hi,

Sorry for logging this here. I am not sure which other repo to log it in.

Since upgrading from dotnet core 1.03 on mac to 1.04 the xunit tests that we were running just fine previously on both windows and mac and debian are failing... well they are just not running on windows and also in Visual Studio for Mac. (dotnet cli still runs the tests fine in mac and debian)

Not sure but it does seem like it has something to do with threading. I have had a few new issues with async Tasks that have no return statement failing in 1.04, program executes fine but the thread seems to get lost and never returns to the control thread or gets aborted when the program terminates.

I hope this helps you solve these issues as I have found VS for mac pretty nice in a few ways and would like to see it as a viable option for our dev, as it is though we run our test suite and only a handful of tests ever get executed properly.

On windows when we ran migrate and executed the tests for our coverage reporting they would also work with 1.03 but now they don't execute properly.

Thanks.

",{},{}
