```
from __future__ import print_function
import json
from os.path import join, dirname
from watson_developer_cloud import SpeechToTextV1
from watson_developer_cloud.websocket import RecognizeCallback

try:
   import http.client as http_client
except ImportError:
   import httplib as http_client
   
http_client.HTTPConnection.debuglevel = 1

speech_to_text = SpeechToTextV1(
    username='myusername',
    password='mypassword',
    url='https://stream.watsonplatform.net/speech-to-text/api')

try:
        with open(join(dirname(__file__), '../resources/speech.wav'),'rb') as audio_file:            
        print(json.dumps(speech_to_text.recognize(audio=audio_file,content_type='audio/wav'),indent=2))
except Exception as e:
        print('errore: '+str(e))
```

#### python sdk version
1.4.1
#### python version
Tried with 3.6.3 on windows and with default python versions (2.7 and 3) on linuxmint
