I have a ModelSchema class in one of my folders that uses models.py from the other folder. SQLAlchemy by default solves this problem by using the string name of the class but I get circular import errors in Marshmallow SQLAlchemy. Is there a way to solve this? Or shoud I change my structure? ",{},{}
15236,IssuesEvent,2017-10-30 00:00:27+00:00,40094312,pyserial/pyserial,279819,egnor,10537924,pyserial,opened,write() on POSIX can throw SerialTimeoutException even when it succeeds,[],[],0,"Hi hi,

The serialposix.py implementation (https://github.com/pyserial/pyserial/blob/master/serial/serialposix.py) handles a nonzero timeout in this way:

```
            try:
                n = os.write(self.fd, d)
                if timeout.is_non_blocking:
                    ...
                elif not timeout.is_infinite:
                    # when timeout is set, use select to wait for being ready
                    # with the time left as timeout
                    if timeout.expired():
                        raise writeTimeoutError
                    abort, ready, _ = select.select([self.pipe_abort_write_r], [self.fd], [], timeout.time_left())
                    if abort:
                        os.read(self.pipe_abort_write_r, 1000)
                        break
                    if not ready:
                        raise writeTimeoutError
```

_Even if the os.write() succeeds entirely_, this will raise writeTimeoutError (an instance of SerialTimeoutException) if the timeout has expired by the time it reaches the ""if timeout.expired()"" statement. This is trivial to reproduce -- set write_timeout to a very small value (like 1e-6) and try to write() something.

Even when write_timeout() is a more reasonable value, this is very flawed logic; depending on exactly how much time it takes to perform the write() (which is potentially up to the vagaries of the scheduler, etc) spurious SerialTimeoutExceptions will be thrown even if the data is partially or completely written successfully. This in turn means the application has no way of knowing how much data was written and life is generally sad.",{},{}
