I just realise that I cant use serial_for_url on loop:// if I instanciate whith do_not_open=True option and configure port and open() later.
The error message is: could not open port loop:// [Errno2] Aucun fichier ou dossier de ce type: 'loop://'
Tested on 3.0a0 and 3.0b1",{},{}
15249,IssuesEvent,2016-11-09 16:40:30+00:00,40094312,pyserial/pyserial,3405461,hetii,10537924,pyserial,opened,CMSPAR bit is never clear when back to other parity setting.,[],[],0,"In serial/serialposix.py there is bug regarding CMSPAR bit.
So its possible to set MARK or SPACE parity, but after that its not possible to back to other parity modes. This bit remains always set.

        # setup parity
        iflag &= ~(termios.INPCK | termios.ISTRIP)
        if self._parity == serial.PARITY_NONE:
            cflag &= ~(termios.PARENB | termios.PARODD)
        elif self._parity == serial.PARITY_EVEN:
            cflag &= ~(termios.PARODD)
            cflag |= (termios.PARENB)
        elif self._parity == serial.PARITY_ODD:
            cflag |= (termios.PARENB | termios.PARODD)
        elif self._parity == serial.PARITY_MARK and plat[:5] == 'linux':
            cflag |= (termios.PARENB | CMSPAR | termios.PARODD)
        elif self._parity == serial.PARITY_SPACE and plat[:5] == 'linux':
            cflag |= (termios.PARENB | CMSPAR)
            cflag &= ~(termios.PARODD)
        else:
            raise ValueError('Invalid parity: %r' % self._parity)",{},{}
