15541,IssuesEvent,2017-10-12 18:30:25+00:00,28774758,ets-labs/python-dependency-injector,1742049,rmk135,11329744,ets-labs,opened,"Add "".provider"" attribute for all providers","[{'id': 184656954, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ets-labs/python-dependency-injector/labels/feature', 'name': 'feature', 'color': 'fbca04', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'rmk135', 'id': 1742049, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/1742049?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rmk135', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/rmk135', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rmk135/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rmk135/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rmk135/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rmk135/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rmk135/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rmk135/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rmk135/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rmk135/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rmk135/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"Idea of this feature is to provide a user-friendly way to inject factories (and other providers...), see example below:

```python
class Models(DeclarativeContainer):
    """"""Domain model component providers container.""""""

    user = Factory(models.users.User)


class Services(DeclarativeContainer):
    """"""Service providers container.""""""

    user_registration = Singleton(services.users.Registration,
                                  user_factory=Models.user.provider)
```",{},{}
15542,IssuesEvent,2016-05-16 15:12:42+00:00,28774758,ets-labs/python-dependency-injector,1742049,rmk135,11329744,ets-labs,closed,"Implement adding of injections for Callable, Factory & Singleton providers","[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ets-labs/python-dependency-injector/labels/feature', 'name': 'feature', 'color': 'fbca04'}]",[],1,"Example syntax:

```python
from dependency_injector import providers

factory = providers.Factory(...)
factory.add_injections(1, 2, 3, a=1, b=2)
```

``Factory.add_injections()`` method should follow the same rules as ``Factory.__init__()``",{},{}
