=========================== 1 error in 0.59 seconds ============================
```

Any thoughts?

Thanks",{},{}
15782,IssuesEvent,2017-11-17 20:56:12+00:00,1292669,django-ses/django-ses,7373924,efischer19,12100228,django-ses,opened,Non-unicode log messages can break on sender name,[],[],0,"Hello! I work at edx.org, where we make use of this library to send bulk emails from educators to learners.

Recently, [we ran into an issue with some Spanish courses](https://openedx.atlassian.net/browse/EDUCATOR-1773). Specifically, [this logging statement](https://github.com/django-ses/django-ses/blob/v0.8.3.1/django_ses/__init__.py#L217-L222) causes a `UnicodeEncodeError` when `message.from_email` contains non-ascii characters. In our case, the `from_email` value is constructed as `{course_title} Course Staff <{some_valid_noreply_addr}>`, and for these courses, the titles contain accented vowels.

It's worth noting that the emails are sent without any issue, the only problem seems to be the logging statements as far as I can tell.

Here is a fairly minimal recreation taken from a pdb session I just ran:

```
(Pdb) from_addr
u'""\xf3\xf3\xf3\xf3\xf3\xf3\xf3\xf3\xf3\xf3\xf3\xf3\xf3\xf3\xf3"" Course Staff <asdasd-no-reply@example.com>'
(Pdb) print ""send_messages.sent from='{}'"".format(from_addr)
*** UnicodeEncodeError: 'ascii' codec can't encode characters in position 1-15: ordinal not in range(128)
(Pdb) print u""send_messages.sent from='{}'"".format(from_addr)
send_messages.sent from='""óóóóóóóóóóóóóóó"" Course Staff <asdasd-no-reply@example.com>'
```

Would there be any drawback to making all log messages unicode by default? I'm happy to put together a PR if you'd like.

Thanks, and have a great weekend!",{},{}
15783,IssuesEvent,2018-08-20 20:45:36+00:00,99273369,NeurodataWithoutBorders/pynwb,1616478,ajtritt,12140348,NeurodataWithoutBorders,closed,Error when creating extensions with 'str' datatype,"[{'id': 661411410, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw2NjE0MTE0MTA=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/NeurodataWithoutBorders/pynwb/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'ee0701', 'default': True}, {'id': 661457897, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw2NjE0NTc4OTc=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/NeurodataWithoutBorders/pynwb/labels/major', 'name': 'major', 'color': 'ededed', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'ajtritt', 'id': 1616478, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjE2MTY0Nzg=', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/1616478?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/ajtritt', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/ajtritt', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/ajtritt/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/ajtritt/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/ajtritt/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/ajtritt/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/ajtritt/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/ajtritt/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/ajtritt/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/ajtritt/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/ajtritt/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",1,"The following code: 

```python
from pynwb.spec import NWBGroupSpec, NWBAttributeSpec, NWBLinkSpec, NWBNamespaceBuilder
from pynwb import get_class, load_namespaces
import os
import warnings


ext_path = '/home/loren/Src/NWB/franklabnwb/fl_extensions'
ns_name = 'franklab'
ns_path = '%s/%s.namespace.yaml' % (ext_path, ns_name)
ext_source = ""%s.extensions.yaml"" % ns_name

ns_builder = NWBNamespaceBuilder('Extensions for use in the the Frank Laboratory', 'franklab')
FL_ClusterQuality_ext = NWBGroupSpec('Frank Lab Cluster Quality Class',
                                                                     attributes=[NWBAttributeSpec('name',
                                                                                                                          'cluster id',
                                                                                                                           'str',
                                                                                                                            required=True),
												 NWBAttributeSpec('isolation_distance',
																  'mountainsort isolation distance metic',
																  'float',
																  required=False),
												 NWBAttributeSpec('noise_overlap',
																  'mountainsort noise overlap metric',
																  'float',
																  required=False)],
									 neurodata_type_def='FL_ClusterQuality',
									 neurodata_type_inc='NWBContainer')


# add the class to the namespace builder
ns_builder.add_spec(ext_source, FL_ClusterQuality_ext)
# create a builder for the namespace
ns_builder.export(ns_path)



# test
load_namespaces(ns_path)

FL_ClusterQuality = get_class('FL_ClusterQuality', ns_name)
help(FL_ClusterQuality)

```

Produces 

> Help on class FL_ClusterQuality in module abc:
> 
> class FL_ClusterQuality(pynwb.core.NWBContainer)
>  |  The base class to any NWB types.
>  |  
>  |  The purpose of this class is to provide a mechanism for representing hierarchical
>  |  relationships in neurodata.
>  |  
>  |  Method resolution order:
>  |      FL_ClusterQuality
>  |      pynwb.core.NWBContainer
>  |      pynwb.core.NWBBaseType
>  |      pynwb.form.container.Container
>  |      builtins.object
>  |  
>  |  Methods defined here:
>  |  
>  |  __init__(*args, **kwargs)
>  |      __init__(source, name, parent=None, container_source=None, isolation_distance=None, noise_overlap=None)
>  |      
>  |      
>  |      
>  |      Args:
>  |          source (str): a description of where this NWBContainer came from
>  |          name (None): cluster id
>  |          parent (NWBContainer): the parent Container for this Container
>  |          container_source (object): the source of this Container e.g. file name
>  |          isolation_distance (float): mountainsort isolation distance metic
>  |          noise_overlap (float): mountainsort noise overlap metric

Note the (None) datatype for name.  As a result, attempting to save an NWBFile with this object in it fails. 

I think this means that the 'str' datatype isn't properly assigned when the extension is created.
",{},{}
