15949,IssuesEvent,2018-07-26 16:58:58+00:00,40328394,angr/angr,2498805,rhelmot,12520807,angr,closed,vsprintf and sprintf wrong behavior on buffer size of 0,[],[],0,"Hello,

I've encounter the following case:
```
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdarg.h>

void PrintFError ( const char * format, ... )
{
  va_list args;
  va_start (args, format);
  vsnprintf (NULL,0,format, args);
  perror (buffer);
  va_end (args);
}

void vs_test() {
        char szFileName[]=""myfile.txt"";
        PrintFError (""Error opening '%s'"",szFileName);
}
```

Also a compiled binary is attached (elf arm 32 bit)

According to the following stackoverflow question:  
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/37432797/snprintf-negative-zero-value-of-buffer-size

If you pass 0 on the size of the buffer the function shouldn't write to the buffer and so it can also be NULL.

The current implementation call memory.store either way and so when I set hook on mem_write the hook being called although no write should be happening.

It caused in: 
https://github.com/angr/angr/blob/master/angr/procedures/libc/vsnprintf.py
and 
https://github.com/angr/angr/blob/master/angr/procedures/libc/snprintf.py

I will make a pull request fixing this issue.

[vsnprintf.zip](https://github.com/angr/angr/files/2231666/vsnprintf.zip)

Edit:
This is the pull request: https://github.com/angr/angr/pull/1154",{},{}
15974,IssuesEvent,2017-08-09 00:21:30+00:00,40328394,angr/angr,2498805,rhelmot,12520807,angr,closed,Hooking extern functions in linux kernel module (ARM),[],[],13,"Using `Project.hook_symbol('strncmp', strncmphook)` doesn't appear to work in my kernel module. I can hook each call site individually but that obviously takes more manual analysis time. Essentially, I want this symbol to resolve to a SimProcedure:
```
In [115]: b = angr.Project(""./led-kmod.ko"")
     ...: x=b.loader.main_bin.get_symbol('strncmp')
     ...: print ""%s is at %s"" % (x.name, hex(x.addr))
     ...: 
WARNING | 2017-07-27 14:55:10,285 | cle.loader | The main binary is a position-independent executable. It is being loaded with a base address of 0x400000.
strncmp is at 0x0
```
Hooking each `BL strncmp` call site with `b.hook(addr, strncmphook, length=4)` works, where `strncmphook` is a function that manually resolves R0, R1 and R2 to compare the strings at those addresses and sets R0 appropriately.

How can I properly hook this `extern` symbol?",{},{}
