16091,IssuesEvent,2018-07-01 17:18:19+00:00,16469697,mps-youtube/mps-youtube,1438488,Razesdark,12987682,mps-youtube,closed,reading keywords from .txt to search,[],[],0,"**Hello everyone.**

_I'm new on this forum and I'm not english so excuse me if I make some mistakes writing my post...._

I just discover mps-youtube and it's amazing! Thanks guys for the job!!!
I  ask myself if it's possible to make search with keyword by reading in a txt file line by line. (I know MPSyt can read url line by line in txt file but what about keyword)

I explain:
Every time I hear a good sound, I write the artist and the title in a txt file line by line (music.txt).
So I'm searching for a program able to read each keyword on a line, launching the search on youtube and write the URL of the best result (quality, lengh...) in an another .txt file (result.txt for exemple)
After that, I can copy the result.txt in Word, clicking the hypertext link, checking if it's the good one and make personnal playlist on my youtube channel. (Maybe the programm could manage errors by creating an error.txt file with the copy of the line that doesn't make result on a search...) _(My txt file is above 500 lines actually...)_

So I asked a developpement team to help me searching for a solution and one of them tell me about mpsyoutube...

So If someone can tell me if it's possible or if it exist another way to do this, it would be great!
Thanks all of you.

Mozza
",{},{}
