16172,IssuesEvent,2018-03-15 12:33:02+00:00,98255530,source-foundry/ufolint,380829,madig,13209832,source-foundry,closed,Scope of UFOLint?,[],[],8,"Hi!
I'm wondering if it would be within the scope of the project to check the semantics of UFO fields. E.g.:

- Presence of openTypeNameVersion, UniqueID fields which are automatically generated by ufo2ft
- versionMajor/Minor disagree with what's in openTypeNameVersion
- Some glyph roundtripped from a .glyphs has a metrics key but the numeric side-bearing doesn't match up

Maybe even something as simple as importing a local module that runs all the checks one wants.",{},{}
16186,IssuesEvent,2016-05-26 08:53:15+00:00,43645564,ganga-devs/ganga,1102021,rob-c,13271048,ganga-devs,closed,DIRAC-ui broken on cvmfs,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ganga-devs/ganga/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ganga-devs/ganga/labels/DIRAC', 'name': 'DIRAC', 'color': 'd4c5f9'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ganga-devs/ganga/labels/help%20wanted', 'name': 'help wanted', 'color': 'bfe5bf'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ganga-devs/ganga/labels/question', 'name': 'question', 'color': 'fbca04'}]",[],3,"Hi all,

I can't seem to generate an lsst proxy using the dirac-ui on cvmfs due to something being out of date (I suspect a voms proxy but this is not my area of expertise).

Is there a plan/policy which sorts out the voms proxies on the cvmfs install?

Would it be more sane to manage the voms proxies in a user area so that these can be updated by Ganga once the user needs them rather than wait for cvmfs to cycle?

Thanks,

Rob",{},{}
16189,IssuesEvent,2016-05-13 12:08:14+00:00,43645564,ganga-devs/ganga,1102021,rob-c,13271048,ganga-devs,closed,GangaDirac RTUtils incompatible with GangaDataset,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ganga-devs/ganga/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ganga-devs/ganga/labels/Core', 'name': 'Core', 'color': 'd4c5f9'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ganga-devs/ganga/labels/DIRAC', 'name': 'DIRAC', 'color': 'd4c5f9'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ganga-devs/ganga/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '009800'}]",[],1,"The DiracRTHUtils is incompatible with GangaDataset due to some LHCb specific features from LHCbDataset being tested/over-used.

I've got some fixes for this in my GangaLSST branch that I plan to factor out. I'm also exposing a lot of the GangaDataset features to the GPI as I can create this object from the GPI so I should be able to manipulate it.

I'll sort out a PR later today to try and address this.",{},{}
16205,IssuesEvent,2018-02-05 10:54:52+00:00,43645564,ganga-devs/ganga,4319174,egede,13271048,ganga-devs,closed,Arrows and segfault and concurrent live sessions,[],[],8,"I often use the arrows to go up and down the history of commands. Sometimes I click on the down arrow one time too many and ganga segfaults. I then have to wait few tenths of seconds to restart it. 

I tried with python and python shell doesn't crash for the extra clicks. This gives really the impression of fragility to be honest.

Also when one mistakenly starts more than one ganga session, it would be good to have a ""steal"" option or get an error message maybe proposing to close the other session and the current session to exit before it tries to start anything. Instead of this long series of messages for several minutes. After all ganga knows it in the first two lines there is another live session. 

