16330,IssuesEvent,2018-01-30 16:46:52+00:00,15037172,webrecorder/pywb,1015759,ikreymer,13686290,webrecorder,closed,Pywb requires restart in order to know about additions to an collections archive,[],[],7,"In order to have pywb recognize that a new warc file has been added (including index.cdxj update) it must be restarted.
Is there an configuration that allows pywb to automatically know about such additions or an endpoint that can be configured to allow such functionality?

Use case: 
User initiated a crawl via Heritrix through WAIL and it finishes. WAIl then utilizes wb-manager to add the produced warc to the collection (reindexing of  the collection happens).
WAIL then informs the user their collection has been updated, the user then queries pywb through WAIL about the addition and receives a reply of not found.

@machawk1
