16411,IssuesEvent,2018-02-01 01:03:51+00:00,46374199,IntelRealSense/librealsense,1797963,jpapon,14095512,IntelRealSense,opened,High CPU Utilization,[],[],0,"This is listed in #744 and #707, but since both of those are closed I am opening a new issue.
OpenMP causes librealsense to consume a full CPU core - this is likely due to the use of `#pragma omp parallel for schedule(dynamic)` .

Disabling OpenMP in CMake with `-DBUILD_WITH_OPENMP=false` is a workaround, but this could increase latency at high-framerates/resolutions.",{},{}
