16560,IssuesEvent,2018-06-18 21:06:21+00:00,92238803,openai/baselines,12174271,sidmysore,14957082,openai,opened,Why multiply mean by 0.0 in PPO1 mlp_policy?,[],[],0,"I was looking over the code in [mlp_policy.py](https://github.com/openai/baselines/blob/master/baselines/ppo1/mlp_policy.py) and I noticed this on [line 39](https://github.com/openai/baselines/blob/a6b1bc70f156dc45c0da49be8e80941a88021700/baselines/ppo1/mlp_policy.py#L39) (at least as of the current master):

`pdparam = tf.concat([mean, mean * 0.0 + logstd], axis=1)`

Could someone explain why the mean is multiplied by 0 before adding logstd? Unless I'm misunderstanding something, wouldn't it be equivalent to simply do this?:

`pdparam = tf.concat([mean, logstd], axis=1)`

Was the 0.0 perhaps meant to be a placeholder for something? The commit history seems to indicate that this line has been there since the file was created. Any clarification would be appreciated.

Thanks!",{},{}
