18272,IssuesEvent,2018-07-20 14:58:34+00:00,4351480,laspy/laspy,6976972,romulogoncalves,24229635,laspy,opened,create LAS file: reset the number of points.,[],[],0,"We are trying to create a LAS file with less points than the input file. Here is the code:
```
in_pc = File(tile_path, mode='r')
header = in_pc.header.copy()
header.point_records_count = (tile_size / grid_cell_size) * (tile_size / grid_cell_size)
in_pc.close()

out_LAS = File(tile_out_path, mode = ""w"", header=header)

print(""The number of points is: %d "" % out_LAS.header.point_records_count)
```

The print statement shows that we the open file has a header saying 4 points
```
The number of points is: 4
```

However, laspy complains that the number of records in the header is different than the number of records to be added when we set `X`:
```
out_LAS.x = x
```
Gives:
```
WARNING: laspy found invalid data in header.point_records_count.
                            Header.point_records_count = 0, and 4 records actually detected.
                            Attempting to correct mismatch.
```

We do not understand why the [manager](https://github.com/laspy/laspy/blob/master/laspy/base.py#L164) is not using the new `point_records_count`:
```
if self.manager.header.point_records_count
```

How is manager initiated? We thought it would use the header information. Should the reset be done in a different way?",{},{}
