18369,IssuesEvent,2018-05-30 07:09:15+00:00,35531022,opendatacube/datacube-core,39038859,santoshamohan,26125288,opendatacube,opened,Query search fails when time range is 'None',[],[],0,"### Expected behaviour
When time range is 'None', query anything that need processing.

### Actual behaviour
Query is not successful when time range is 'None' (if we want to query products by time range).

### Steps to reproduce the behaviour
Include the following test code in the test_query.py and run a pytest on test_query.py file.

    query = Query(index=mock_index, time=None)
    assert 'time' not in query.search

### Environment information
Open Data Cube core, version 1.6rc1+28.ga69dfff

Module files used:
  1) pbs                2) git/2.9.5          3) dea-env/20180405   4) udunits/2.1.24     5) dea/20180515",{},{}
18374,IssuesEvent,2018-07-13 03:49:52+00:00,35531022,opendatacube/datacube-core,108979,omad,26125288,opendatacube,closed,Silent dataset location modification when using `datacube dataset <add|update>`,"[{'id': 646828111, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw2NDY4MjgxMTE=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/opendatacube/datacube-core/labels/usability', 'name': 'usability', 'color': 'e99695', 'default': False}]",[],0,"### Expected behaviour

`datacube dataset add/update` should report that a new dataset location was recorded in the database.

### Actual behaviour

`datacube -vv dataset add` reports:

```
WARNING Duplicate dataset, not inserting: f5b8dfa5-47c5-489d-ab2f-d518c72d8a70
```

while `datacube -vv dataset update` reports:

```
INFO No changes detected for dataset f5b8dfa5-47c5-489d-ab2f-d518c72d8a70
```

Yet dataset location is modified as can be confirmed by `datacube dataset info`

```
id: f5b8dfa5-47c5-489d-ab2f-d518c72d8a70
product: ls8_nbar_albers
status: active
indexed: 2017-09-07 15:36:39.485455+10:00
locations:
- file:///Users/kirill/datacube/ls8_nbar_pq/tmp2.nc
- file:///Users/kirill/datacube/ls8_nbar_pq/tmp.nc
- file:///Users/kirill/datacube/ls8_nbar_pq/LS8_OLI_NBAR_3577_5_-37_20161005003349000000.nc                                                                  
fields:
    format: NetCDF
    instrument: OLI_TIRS
    lat: {begin: -33.77978845211354, end: -33.54258935760496}
    lon: {begin: 138.1793664303201, end: 138.5168418084227}
    platform: LANDSAT_8
    product_type: nbar
    time: {begin: '2016-10-05T00:33:49', end: '2016-10-05T00:33:49'}
```

### Steps to reproduce the behaviour

In a test database find some dataset, make a copy of the netcdf file. Call `datacube -vv dataset add` on the copy. Then run `datacube dataset info <uuid>` and observe that locations part has been augmented with a new file.

 

